project.name: Flow
project.description:
The idea of the flow domain is to connect pairs of points on a grid with a continuous line such that no two lines cross one another. This is a popular casual game on tablets, desktops, and the internet. The current implementation treats each line as a path an agent must take, filling in the grid as they move around. The number of pairs corresponds to the number of agents in the domain.
Designed by Christian Muise, 2012

action.precondition: self.at = from and to.free and from.connected->includes(to)
action.postcondition: self.at = to and to.colour = self and to.free = false
